timeline.event: Jupiter is clearly visible to the naked eye and has been known since antiquity
Galileo Galilei discovers Jupiter's four largest moons
Pioneer 10 is the first man-made probe to visit Jupiter
Voyagers 1 and 2 arrive at Jupiter, observing the planets ring system for the first time
Galileo orbiter arrives at Jupiter remaining in the Jovian system until 2003
Cassini probe passes Jupiter en route to Saturn
New Horizons probe passes Jupiter en route to Pluto
Juno probe enters polar orbit around Jupiter
